{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 32,
  "title": "第三十二章（知止）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "道恆无名"
    },
    {
      "text": "楃唯小 而天下弗敢臣"
    },
    {
      "text": "侯王若能守之 萬物將自賓 天地相合 以俞甘洛 民莫之令而自均焉"
    },
    {
      "text": "始制有名 名亦既有 夫亦將知止 知止所以不殆"
    },
    {
      "text": "俾道之在天下也 猶小浴之與江海也"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道能陰能陽，能弛能張，能存能亡，故無常名也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道樸雖小，微妙無形，天下不敢有臣使道者也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "侯王若能守道無為，萬物將自賓，服從於德也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 31
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "侯王動作能與天相應和，天即降下甘露善瑞也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 23,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天降甘露善瑞，則萬物莫有教令之者，皆自均調若一也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "始，道也。有名，萬物也。道無名能制於有名，無形，能制於有形也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 5,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "既，盡也。有名之物，盡有情欲，叛道離德，故身毀辱也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能法道行德，天亦將自知之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天知之，則神靈祐助，不復危怠。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "譬言道之在天下，與人相應和，如川谷與江海相流通也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道，無形不繫，常不可名，以無名為常。故曰「道常無名」也。樸之為物，以無為心也，亦無名，故將得道，莫若守樸，夫智者可以能臣也，勇者可以武使也，巧者可以事役也，力者可以重任也，樸之為物，憒然不偏，近於無有，故曰「莫能臣也」。抱樸無為，不以物累其真，不以欲害其神，則物自賓而道自得也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言天地相合，則甘露不求而自降；我守其真性無為，則民不令而自均也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "始制，謂樸散始為官長之時也。始制官長，不可不立名分，以定尊卑，故始制有名也，過此以往，將爭錐刀之末，故曰「名亦既有」，夫亦將知止也，遂任名以號物，則失治之母也，故知止所以不殆也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "川谷之求江與海，非江海召之，不召不求而自歸者，世行道於天下者，不令而自均，不求而自得，故曰「猶川谷之與江海」也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
